    "text": "Erdős Problem #616: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $r\\geq 3$. For an $r$-uniform hypergraph $G$ let $\\tau(G)$ denote the covering number (or transversal number), the minimum size of a set of vertices which includes at least one from each edge in $G$.\n\nDetermine the best possible $t$ such that, if $G$ is an $r$-uniform hypergraph $G$ where every subgraph $G'$ on at most $3r-3$ vertices has $\\tau(G')\\leq 1$, we have $\\tau(G)\\leq t$. Prize: no. Tags: graph theory.",
